<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">Named after its original habitat as an endophytic fungus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="46" type="holotype">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">MFLU 18-0001</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">Culture characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName genus="Colonies" lsidName="Colonies" pageId="21" pageNumber="46" rank="genus">Colonies</taxonomicName>
on PDA (Figure 2, FE101), superficial, dark olivaceous with circular rings with filiform edge and rough and raised on media surface; reverse dark olivaceous. 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Incertae sedis Basidiomycota" family="Incertae sedis Basidiomycota" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Mycelium" order="Incertae sedis Basidiomycota" pageId="21" pageNumber="46" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Mycelium</taxonomicName>
composed of branched, pale-brown to dark-brown, thick-walled, guttulate, hyphae, with cells sub-globose to ovoid in shape. Not sporulating in culture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="46" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="46">
THAILAND, Ranong, Muang, on healthy leaves of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Freycinetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Freycinetia" order="Pandanales" pageId="21" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Freycinetia</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Incertae sedis Basidiomycota" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Mycelium" order="Incertae sedis Basidiomycota" pageId="21" pageNumber="46" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Pandanaceae</taxonomicName>
), 3 December 2016, S. Tibpromma FE101 (MFLU 18-0001, holotype); HKAS100847, paratype, ex-type living cultures, MFLUCC 17-0545 = KUMCC 17-0263.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="46" type="genbank numbers">
